    • Method Detail

      • addChild

        public void addChild(FileSystemEntry child)
              throws IOException

        Adds a child entry to this directory. The child entry data is written to the local file system.

        Parameters:
        child - the child entry to add.
        Throws:
        IOException - if this directory already contains an entry with the same name, there's not enough free space on the file system, or an I/O error occurs.

      • unlink

        public void unlink(String child)
            throws IOException

        Removes (unlinks) the child entry denoted by child from this directory.

        Parameters:
        child - the name of the child entry to remove.
        Throws:
        IOException - if this directory doesn't contain an entry named child, or an I/O error occurs.
